</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15BF7DF9454CFFD8A6E9FA46FE124EA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5D1A2E72454CFFD8A6E9FA46FE124EA1" blockId="0.[151,1437,1249,1769]" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A6E9FA46FE8F4DC1" box="[199,316,1421,1445]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" reason="1">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A6E9FA46FE864DC1" bold="true" box="[199,309,1421,1445]" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Males of the genus (
<figureCitation id="C59E32F7454CFFD8A40DFA46FD304DC1" box="[547,643,1421,1445]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[172,1407,851,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-372@1.[166,1422,847,1824]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lithosiina spp., adults. 2–4 – type species of the genera Lobilema and Ligulosia. Depositories of the specimens: 1, 2 and 4 in ANHRT; 3 in NHRS (Photo by T. Malm, ©NHRS)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5572071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5572071/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Figs 1–3</figureCitation>
) are reminiscent of those of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="9AA555F1454CFFD8A201FA46FA984DC1" authority="Kruger, 2015" authorityName="Kruger" authorityYear="2015" box="[1071,1323,1421,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Ligulosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A201FA46FB274DC1" box="[1071,1172,1421,1445]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Ligulosia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="39345383454CFFD8A2B2FA45FA984DC1" author="Kruger, M." box="[1180,1323,1421,1446]" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" refId="ref2015" refString="Kruger, M. (2015) Generic classification of Afrotropical footman moths sensu stricto (Lepidoptera: Erebidae: Arctiinae: Lithosiini (partim. )). Transvaal Museum Monograph. Vol. 15. Ditsong National Museum of Natural History, Pretoria, 176 pp." type="book" year="2015">Krüger, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(the comparison is based on the 
<typeStatus id="821E90D0454CFFD8A7B4FA79FE7B4DAE" box="[410,456,1458,1482]" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="9AA555F1454CFFD8A403FA7AFBB84DAD" authority="(Aurivillius, 1910))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[557,1035,1457,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Ligulosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costimaculata">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A403FA7AFC834DAD" box="[557,816,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Ligulosia costimaculata</emphasis>
(Aurivillius, 1910))
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C59E32F7454CFFD8A235FA7AFBEE4DAD" box="[1051,1117,1457,1481]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1848,1872]" captionTargetBox="[172,1407,851,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-372@1.[166,1422,847,1824]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lithosiina spp., adults. 2–4 – type species of the genera Lobilema and Ligulosia. Depositories of the specimens: 1, 2 and 4 in ANHRT; 3 in NHRS (Photo by T. Malm, ©NHRS)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5572071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5572071/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) but are distinguished by the presence of a costal lobe on the forewing. The structures of the male genital capsule of the two genera are similar (
<figureCitation id="C59E32F7454CFFD8A343FA1EFF734E75" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[170,1404,184,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Lithosiina spp., male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens: 5, 6 and 8 in ANHRT; 7 in NHRS (Photo by T. Malm, ©NHRS)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5572073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5572073/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Figs 5–8</figureCitation>
) but in 
<taxonomicName id="9AA555F1454CFFD8A737FA32FECD4E75" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1910" box="[281,382,1529,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lobilema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A737FA32FECD4E75" box="[281,382,1529,1553]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Lobilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the anellus is sclerotised and bearing heavily sclerotised and apically spinulose lateral lobes (an autapomorphic feature), a structure supporting the aedeagus ventrally while the juxta is weakly sclerotised, narrow and highly likely lacking a supporting function. Unlike in 
<taxonomicName id="9AA555F1454CFFD8A4C9F98AFCFF4E3D" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1910" box="[743,844,1601,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lobilema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A4C9F98AFCFF4E3D" box="[743,844,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Lobilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the juxta of 
<taxonomicName id="9AA555F1454CFFD8A5CFF98AFBF54E3D" authorityName="Kruger" authorityYear="2015" box="[993,1094,1601,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Ligulosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A5CFF98AFBF54E3D" box="[993,1094,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Ligulosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is large, triangular with a deep medio-basal incision and two short distal processes, heavily sclerotised apically, fused with the membranous anellus ventrally and supporting the aedeagus. Additionally, the saccular process of 
<taxonomicName id="9AA555F1454CFFD8A5B9F942FC4F4EC5" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1910" box="[919,1020,1673,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lobilema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A5B9F942FC4F4EC5" box="[919,1020,1673,1697]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Lobilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is setose dorsally and apically whereas it is smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="9AA555F1454CFFD8A718F966FE284EA1" authorityName="Kruger" authorityYear="2015" box="[310,411,1709,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Ligulosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FD1F260454CFFD8A718F966FE284EA1" box="[310,411,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="447">Ligulosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
